I like monochrome icons in my status bar and the FDEMC icon was not cutting it. I made a replacement. These instructions worked for MacOS X Snow Leopard and *may* work for Lion (untested):

1. Download fdemc_icons.zip and upzip.

2. From Terminal, execute (each command should one line):

$ sudo cp /usr/local/ppc-3.2.0-190/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint.png \
  /usr/local/ppc-3.2.0-190/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint-orig.png

$ sudo cp FDEEndpoint-custom.png \
  /usr/local/ppc-3.2.0-190/bin/FDEStatusMenu.app/Contents/Resources/FDEEndpoint.png

3. Re-login
